    "text": "Joseph Epstein is correct that spouses who suffered in difficult unions deserve a Noble Prize retroactively (“Your Spouse Is No Prize? You Deserve a Nobel,” op-ed, May 12).\nThough Mohandas Gandhi, India’s leader of the freedom movement, deserved a Nobel Prize for nonviolence and peace (but never got one), Gandhi’s wife, Kasturba, who long suffered Gandhi’s strict principals, dogma and notions, should not be forgotten and surely deserves a Nobel Prize as part of a couple who worked together for the good of their country.\n... ",
